data.meta_description:
857 likes, 16 comments - expedia on January 21, 2020: "#DidYouKnow that Spokane is the childhood home of Bing Crosby? Although the star was born in Tacoma, Washington, his family moved across the state when he was 6 years old. The Crosby home is located in Gonzaga University and open to visitors as a museum, complete with records, trophies, and his Oscar for Going My Way!
